[LAUGHTER]

00:03:10.390 --> 00:03:11.224
Absolutely horrible.

00:03:11.224 --> 00:03:12.890
It was known for its
cheesecake, but you

00:03:12.890 --> 00:03:15.130
know what happens when you
get famous for cheesecake,

00:03:15.130 --> 00:03:17.920
you sort of cut corners and it
becomes inedible after a while.

00:03:17.920 --> 00:03:20.710
But tourists kept flocking
in for a while until they,

00:03:20.710 --> 00:03:21.320
you know.

00:03:21.320 --> 00:03:27.060
So the thing went bust
right after my book.

00:03:27.060 --> 00:03:31.254
And the problem
that Lindy-- there

00:03:31.254 --> 00:03:32.920
is something named
after that restaurant

00:03:32.920 --> 00:03:34.840
called the Lindy effect.

00:03:34.840 --> 00:03:37.070
Now what is the Lindy effect?

00:03:37.070 --> 00:03:38.740
It was discovered
in that restaurant

00:03:38.740 --> 00:03:41.410
by actors, that plays--

00:03:41.410 --> 00:03:43.940
because the
restaurant specialized

00:03:43.940 --> 00:03:47.920
in giving cheap coffee
or undrinkable coffee

00:03:47.920 --> 00:03:49.270
to unemployed actors.

00:03:49.270 --> 00:03:51.840
So when you're
unemployed actor--

00:03:51.840 --> 00:03:54.880
actors by the way, are usually
unemployed, particularly

00:03:54.880 --> 00:03:55.910
on Broadway.

00:03:55.910 --> 00:03:59.510
So they would sit down and
talk about plays, all right?

00:03:59.510 --> 00:04:03.340
So they discovered
that a play that

00:04:03.340 --> 00:04:06.280
had been around for 200
days had an extra 200

00:04:06.280 --> 00:04:08.290
days of life expectancy.

00:04:08.290 --> 00:04:10.840
And 1,000 days, 1,000 more days.

00:04:10.840 --> 00:04:14.880
It was discovered and became
known as the Lindy effect.

00:04:14.880 --> 00:04:16.930
And about every
single generation

00:04:16.930 --> 00:04:20.269
of mathematicians had tried
to model it, and each--

00:04:20.269 --> 00:04:23.740
the models always work, but
complete different models,

00:04:23.740 --> 00:04:24.690
all right?

00:04:24.690 --> 00:04:26.110
And the last
iteration is the one

00:04:26.110 --> 00:04:28.930
I've been working,
on Lindy effect.

00:04:28.930 --> 00:04:31.150
How do I use the Lindy effect?

00:04:31.150 --> 00:04:32.380
Well, very simple.

00:04:32.380 --> 00:04:35.440
When I write, when I started
"Fooled by Randomness,"

00:04:35.440 --> 00:04:39.030
if you want a book to
survive, how do you write?

00:04:39.030 --> 00:04:40.084
Can someone tell me?

00:04:40.084 --> 00:04:41.500
How do you make
your book survive?

00:04:41.500 --> 00:04:42.474
What's the trick?

00:04:42.474 --> 00:04:44.390
If you want people to
read your book 10 years,

00:04:44.390 --> 00:04:45.770
or 20 years from now?

00:04:45.770 --> 00:04:48.824
If you will have any
chance of that happening?

00:04:48.824 --> 00:04:50.369
AUDIENCE: Make somebody hate it.

00:04:50.369 --> 00:04:51.910
NASSIM TALEB: That
works, but there's

00:04:51.910 --> 00:04:52.810
got to be something else.

00:04:52.810 --> 00:04:53.440
What else?

00:04:53.440 --> 00:04:54.300
AUDIENCE: Write another one.

00:04:54.300 --> 00:04:55.133
NASSIM TALEB: Sorry?

00:04:55.133 --> 00:04:56.854
AUDIENCE: Write another one.

00:04:56.854 --> 00:04:58.020
NASSIM TALEB: That may work.

00:04:58.020 --> 00:05:00.990
Showed that you-- like the
"Incerto" is not body parts,

00:05:00.990 --> 00:05:02.020
but it's one whole.

00:05:02.020 --> 00:05:02.520
Yes?

00:05:02.520 --> 00:05:04.410
AUDIENCE: Use all the ideas.

00:05:04.410 --> 00:05:06.210
NASSIM TALEB: Very good.

00:05:06.210 --> 00:05:07.200
Use all ideas.

00:05:07.200 --> 00:05:09.422
By the Lindy effect,
an old technology

00:05:09.422 --> 00:05:11.505
has a huge survival advantage
over new technology.

00:05:14.490 --> 00:05:17.430
I'm not saying that the future
will not be technological,

00:05:17.430 --> 00:05:19.890
but I'm saying that
what will be displaced

00:05:19.890 --> 00:05:24.070
is the newer technology,
not the old technology.

00:05:24.070 --> 00:05:26.870
So the way-- if you
want to write something

00:05:26.870 --> 00:05:31.580
that can be read 20 years from
now, or hope to be read 20--

00:05:31.580 --> 00:05:36.260
make sure it could be read
by someone 20 years ago.

00:05:36.260 --> 00:05:38.060
So protect yourself
backwards in time.

00:05:38.060 --> 00:05:39.860
It's much easier
than go forward.

00:05:39.860 --> 00:05:44.560
Had someone read the
book in 1960, 1980, would

00:05:44.560 --> 00:05:48.560
he or she have--

00:05:48.560 --> 00:05:51.890
would it have been interested in
the message, in the treatment?

00:05:51.890 --> 00:05:52.835
Yes, no?

00:05:52.835 --> 00:05:55.340
If yes, that's
exactly how you do it.

00:05:55.340 --> 00:05:57.110
So it's basically backwards.

00:05:57.110 --> 00:05:59.644
People who think
that they have to be

00:05:59.644 --> 00:06:01.310
technological for
their work to survive,

00:06:01.310 --> 00:06:05.590
it's the exact opposite by the
Lindy effect, simple logic.

00:06:05.590 --> 00:06:08.960
And effectively, if you
want to predict the future,

00:06:08.960 --> 00:06:10.970
you can't predict
what new will happen.

00:06:10.970 --> 00:06:13.477
Nobody predicted Google.

00:06:13.477 --> 00:06:15.560
Your grandparents didn't
think that you guys would

00:06:15.560 --> 00:06:22.940
be wearing gym clothes with
dog friendly things delivering

00:06:22.940 --> 00:06:24.210
sushi for free, OK?

00:06:27.200 --> 00:06:30.140
And cappuccino, actually
a very good cappuccino.

00:06:30.140 --> 00:06:34.880
I mean, I remember when I first
came to New York how it tasted.

00:06:34.880 --> 00:06:36.620
So your grandparents
didn't predict that.

00:06:36.620 --> 00:06:39.950
You cannot predict-- but
you can predict something,

00:06:39.950 --> 00:06:44.060
which is that what is recent
will be replaced by something

00:06:44.060 --> 00:06:45.550
more recent.

00:06:45.550 --> 00:06:49.380
So it's easier to predict
that what is fragile can break

00:06:49.380 --> 00:06:50.960
and what is-- by
the Lindy effect.

00:06:50.960 --> 00:06:52.575
So it has some--
for some domains.

00:06:52.575 --> 00:06:54.410
It doesn't work for all domains.

