00:09:32.630 --> 00:09:35.240
So I decided to do
that stuff here.

00:09:35.240 --> 00:09:40.220
That's my retirement from
trading, and of course,

00:09:40.220 --> 00:09:41.040
with a mission.

00:09:41.040 --> 00:09:42.536
So I came from
practice to theory,

00:09:42.536 --> 00:09:43.910
and usually people
go from theory

00:09:43.910 --> 00:09:46.285
to practice, particularly in
something very technological

00:09:46.285 --> 00:09:48.570
or something very scientific.

00:09:48.570 --> 00:09:54.940
But this parallels what I
showed in "Antifragile," that--

00:09:54.940 --> 00:10:00.500
and that we had so much
evidence from history--

00:10:00.500 --> 00:10:03.140
that people have the
illusion that technology

00:10:03.140 --> 00:10:07.200
comes from science when
in fact, science come

00:10:07.200 --> 00:10:09.050
from technology more often.

00:10:09.050 --> 00:10:10.640
Except for well
advertised things,

00:10:10.640 --> 00:10:13.385
most sciences came
from technology.

00:10:13.385 --> 00:10:15.260
In other words, they
started doing something,

00:10:15.260 --> 00:10:17.090
didn't know exactly
why it worked,

00:10:17.090 --> 00:10:21.200
and then someone
claimed credit later on.

00:10:21.200 --> 00:10:24.320
What I call lecturing
birds how to fly.

00:10:24.320 --> 00:10:26.660
So starting working with
probabilistic models,

00:10:26.660 --> 00:10:29.060
and I realized that
people who traded

00:10:29.060 --> 00:10:32.270
have a different view of the
world than those who came

00:10:32.270 --> 00:10:34.100
from theory, which is obvious.

00:10:34.100 --> 00:10:36.210
As Yogi Bear, I
would say, in theory

00:10:36.210 --> 00:10:38.210
there is no difference
from theory and practice.

00:10:38.210 --> 00:10:40.084
In practice there is,
so a different mindset.

00:10:40.084 --> 00:10:43.360
But there's something
else I figured out.

00:10:43.360 --> 00:10:46.100
That those who
became practitioners

00:10:46.100 --> 00:10:50.150
after knowing theory
always blew up.

00:10:50.150 --> 00:10:51.980
So in other words,
practice didn't help you

00:10:51.980 --> 00:10:53.051
if you came from theory.

00:10:53.051 --> 00:10:54.800
There's something in
the mindset of people

00:10:54.800 --> 00:10:56.660
who studied economics
or something that

00:10:56.660 --> 00:10:59.990
made them blow up, with the
exception of mathematicians,

00:10:59.990 --> 00:11:01.640
because they're
sort of theory free.

00:11:01.640 --> 00:11:04.835
Mathematics is just some
kind of list of things

00:11:04.835 --> 00:11:06.460
that you believe to
be true, basically.

00:11:08.800 --> 00:11:10.550
And among these things,
there is something

00:11:10.550 --> 00:11:11.622
I call the ludic falalcy.

00:11:11.622 --> 00:11:13.330
Now why am I talking
about ludic fallacy?

00:11:13.330 --> 00:11:15.610
Because when I googled--

00:11:15.610 --> 00:11:20.696
you guys just like, invented
the word, I'm using google.

00:11:20.696 --> 00:11:22.370
When I search for
it on the web--

00:11:22.370 --> 00:11:24.700
[LAUGHTER]

00:11:26.570 --> 00:11:29.030
--I discovered this very
ugly painting by a fellow

00:11:29.030 --> 00:11:34.220
called Isaac McCaslin,
exhibited at the Saatchi gallery

00:11:34.220 --> 00:11:36.350
called the "Ludic Fallacy."

00:11:36.350 --> 00:11:38.960
I don't see the
connection with my work

00:11:38.960 --> 00:11:40.740
and my word, the ludic fallacy.

00:11:40.740 --> 00:11:42.620
But let me explain
the ludic fallacy.

00:11:42.620 --> 00:11:44.940
And I hope it's not
as ugly as this.

00:11:44.940 --> 00:11:48.260
Ludic Fallacy is that the
probability or the risk

00:11:48.260 --> 00:11:52.400
and uncertainty that we
encounter in real life

00:11:52.400 --> 00:11:57.650
has very little to
do with things you

00:11:57.650 --> 00:12:00.440
encounter in casinos and games.

00:12:00.440 --> 00:12:05.130
And ludic is coming
from games in Latin.

00:12:05.130 --> 00:12:08.830
That's why I called
it ludic fallacy.

00:12:08.830 --> 00:12:11.360
So this is sort of like,
preparing the background

00:12:11.360 --> 00:12:12.320
for "Skin in the Game."

